article.headline: Utah Valley edges Weber State 62-59
article.story: OREM, Utah -- Holton Hunsaker scored 14 points and made a critical steal to preserve Utah Valley's 62-59 victory over in-state foe Weber State on Wednesday night. With Utah Valley (4-5) ahead 60-59, Hunsaker missed a free throw with 27 seconds remaining that the Wildcats (1-4) rebounded. But Hunsaker stole the ball from Davion Berry with 8 seconds left and Utah Valley's Hayes Garrity added two free throws before Berry missed a 3-pointer. Garrity scored 13 points while Zach Nelson added 12 points and 10 rebounds for the Wolverines. Berry scored 20 points, including the Wildcats' last seven over the final 4:11. Weber State took its first lead at 46-45 with 10:45 left. The lead changed hands seven times after that. This was Weber State's first game since Nov. 30 after its previously scheduled game on Dec. 7 at Texas-Arlington was cancelled because of inclement weather in the Dallas area that prevented travel.
